{"key":"post-11361534","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>11361534</id>\n<content>Use a boiling pot/kettle, not a crock pot.(perhaps that's what you meant by stock pot?)&amp;nbsp; Crock pots barely heat to boiling when placed on high.&amp;nbsp; You want a rapid boil because it's the steam that sterilizes, not the water.&amp;nbsp; You want the jars on a rack so they're elevated totally out of the water.&amp;nbsp; This prevents the water from splashing up and getting under the foil and into the jars.&amp;nbsp; Use 90 minutes after the time steam begins to escape from under the lid.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>11361880</next>\n<prev>11361205</prev>\n<first>11360603</first>\n<last>11361880</last>\n<when>1257091435</when>\n<utime>11/01/09 06:03 PM</utime>\n</post>"}